            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-Hd1e108">Rubrica 13</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De munitione et custodia locorum</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>¶ De mutatione et custodia locorum. Rubr 13
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>CRontinus Li. 3 ti.
      <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>12. <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-Qd1e125">Alci
        <lb ed="#V" n="71" break="no"/>biades athenis ciuitate sua lacede
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>moniis obsessa veritus negligenti
        <lb ed="#V" n="73" break="no"/>am vigilum denunciauit his qui in stationi
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>bus erant vt obseruarent lumen quod nocte osten
        <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>surus esset ex arce: et ad conspectum eius ipi
        <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>quoque lumina attolerent: quo munere qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>cessasset penam passurum: dum solicite ex
        <lb ed="#V" n="78" break="no"/>peciaretur signum ducis: per vigilatum ab
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>omnibus et suspecte noctis periculum eui
        <lb ed="#V" n="80" break="no"/>tatum est.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-d1e150"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-Qd1e152"> Li. 4. ti. 26 Usus inuenit vt
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>acerrimi canes et sagacissimi in turribus
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>nutriantur qui aduentum hostium odore
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>presentiant latratusque testentur. Anseres
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>quoque non minore solertia noctumos su
        <lb ed="#V" n="85" break="no"/>peruentus clamoribus indicant: nam ingres
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>si capitolinam arcem galli romanum nomen euer
        <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>tissent: nisi clamore anseris excitatus mallius
        <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>restitisset. Mira diligentia siue fortuma vi
        <lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>ros qui vniuersum orbem erant missuri subiugum
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>auis vna seruauit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-d1e178"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-Qd1e180"> Ult. c. quod est epilogus. So <!--294.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="128-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>lertissime caueatur: nequando aut potus in
        <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>opia emergat: aut cibi: quibus malis nulla
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>arte succurritur. Ideoque intra muros tanto
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>plura condenda sunt quinto scitur clausure ten
        <lb ed="#V" n="5" break="no"/>pus in obsidentium consistere voluntate. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-d1e201">
               <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-Qd1e205">¶ Cassiodorus: epistolarum vel. i. e. 16. Ma
        <lb ed="#V" n="7" break="no"/>le constructio loci: tunc queritur quando iam
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>pericula formidantur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-d1e213"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99598-Qd1e215"> Li. 3 e. 49. Muni
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>tio captanda semper in ocio est: quia tunc ma
        <lb ed="#V" n="10" break="no"/>le queritur quoniam necessaria iudicatur. </quote>
            </p>
